[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"498029\">@Andreas Hindborg</span>, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"761630\">@Tamir Duberstein</span>: the CStr refactor breaks linux-next build after I merged Andreas' patches into linux-modules's tree. There's an email from Stephen with the report and he is expecting this to be resolved by tomorrow.</p>\n<p>I've replicated the issue and here's what I have:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">DESCEND</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bpf</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">resolve_btfids</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">CALL</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">checksyscalls</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sh</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">INSTALL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">libsubcmd_headers</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">libmacros</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">so</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\"